Oh, okay thanks. I will try to remove the handler code on "dragover"  and "drop",

But this is only snippet we have in script, regarding drag and drop event preventing users to drop
any elements / images / files into app. but we use webview extensively. users are dropping/ dragging a text/html element from one browserwindow to another browserwindow.

To prevent that we did this code in several, browser-windows. I am not sure whether it might  help, but just thought of adding info to this issue

```
window.addEventListener("dragover", function(e) {
    event.preventDefault();
    return false;
}, false);

window.addEventListener("drop", function(e) {
    event.preventDefault();
    return false;
}, false);

```

Plus i will try to do the same thing in chrome and try between to browser tabs / create a webview in chrome app.  Ah, chrome bug system in sloppy. there are bugs which we have reported 2 years back :(

